items.sentence: Tom has to tell Mary what he wants her to do.
My walk home takes me right past the library.
Tom takes a walk with the kids every evening.
I didn't know Tom and Mary did that together.
I bet you didn't know I was going to do that.
I already know Tom plans to do that tomorrow.
I already knew that Tom was going to do that.
How did Tom know we weren't going to do that?
Everyone knows that Tom won't really do that.
Does Tom know that you want to do that today?
